<subSubSection id="658A2709979E2E8B11F65D3CC4056E4F" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="141906BF4FAE353273653F39977F4785" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">
<taxonomicName id="C37D165D956555D0D62DCAE0B6461BAA" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peryphodes</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 85. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="182EED93BB6ACF25639157FED68DBC7F" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ochthedromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiger">
<emphasis id="FFE01D723DBC83F1071E6AF4273B9CBE" italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Ochthedromus ephippiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1852 by original designation (see Casey 1918: 89). Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="71D5DCF351692D54F06349AD0B497E1B" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4EAEB03E7A83DC62045586CE9E8867E" italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Peryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the Greek suffix - 
<emphasis id="192182F91DF4B442A477C2BA239E9FCF" italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">odes</emphasis>
(likeness), alluding to the resemblance of the adults to those of 
<taxonomicName id="C983E988126385DD403871AAAB01F332" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="831B9CF4243D6253C17C03BE408BDA8E" italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Peryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="71FF1ECB1B2ECD909D96100A86754931" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="6F6107E3DF7DB79124B7C65AAAF8E111" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DB1C1B005EBC018E3D9C1A6CE756E51" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Two North American species in the temperate regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
